question.text:
Following are some features of cockroach:

I. Number of ovarioles in a female cockroach (Ov)

II. The average number of oothecae produced by a female cockroach (Ot)

III. The number of times a nymph of cockroach undergoes moulting (M)

IV. The number of gastric caecae present in cockroach (G)

The correct arrangement of these in their increasing order is

solution.text:
I. Number of ovarioles in a female cockroach (Ov) is 16 (8 ovarioles in one ovary and cockroach has 2 ovaries)

II. The average number of oothecae produced by a female cockroach (Ot) is 9 -10

III. The number of times a nymph of cockroach undergoes moulting (M) is 13 times

IV. The number of gastric caecae present in cockroach (G) is 6-8 which lies between the junction of foregut and hindgut
